Privacy Policy for Zatasha
Effective Date: 04-03-2026

We developed Zatasha, a mobile game available on iOS and Android platforms. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect information when you use the game.

1. Information We Collect

We do not directly collect personally identifiable information such as your name, email address, or phone number.

However, the game collects limited non-personal information necessary for gameplay and basic functionality.

Player Country
We determine the player's country using an IP-based geolocation service. The geolocation service temporarily processes the device’s IP address in order to determine the country.

We do not store the IP address, and only the resulting country information may be stored.

We use the player’s country to:
- Display the player’s country in their profile
- Rank players in regional leaderboards (future feature)
- Analyze power-up usage trends by country
- Offer country-specific promotions or deals
- (Future) Deliver advertisements or promotional content relevant to the player’s region

This information is not used to personally identify players.

2. Third-Party Services

Zatasha integrates third-party services that may collect certain information such as device identifiers, IP address, or usage data according to their own privacy policies.

These services may include:
- Unity Ads
- Google AdMob
- AppLovin (if enabled)
- Facebook SDK (for Facebook login)
- IP Geolocation services used to determine the player’s country
- Unity Authentication services used for player accounts

These services may collect information such as:
- Device identifiers
- IP address
- Advertising identifiers
- Gameplay usage data
- Diagnostic or crash data

We recommend reviewing the privacy policies of these services for more details about how they handle user data.

3. Advertising & Tracking

Zatasha displays advertisements through third-party advertising networks.

These networks may use device identifiers and similar technologies to provide advertisements and measure ad performance.

On iOS devices, the game may request permission through Apple’s App Tracking Transparency (ATT) framework. If granted, this permission allows advertising partners to deliver more relevant advertisements and measure campaign effectiveness.

Allowing or denying tracking permission does not change the number of ads shown, but may affect the relevance of the ads displayed.

Users can modify tracking permissions at any time through their device settings.

4. In-App Purchases

Zatasha offers optional in-app purchases.

All payments are processed by the platform providers:
- Apple App Store
- Google Play Store

We do not collect or store any payment or billing information.

5. Player Accounts

Players may sign in using Unity Authentication or supported login providers.

This allows the game to:
- Save game progress
- Synchronise progress across devices
- Identify players across gameplay sessions

The account system uses unique player identifiers but does not require personal information such as name or email.

6. Children’s Privacy

Zatasha is designed to be a family-friendly game suitable for all ages.

We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. If we become aware that personal information from a child has been collected unintentionally, we will take appropriate steps to delete such information.

7. Data Deletion

Players can delete their game data directly from within the game using the Delete Account / Delete Data option.

When a deletion request is made, we remove the player’s stored game data from our servers.

If you experience issues with data deletion or need assistance, you may contact us at:

support@zatasha.net

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.

If significant changes are made, the updated policy will be published within the game or on the app store listing.

Continued use of the game after updates indicates acceptance of the revised policy.

Contact

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact:

